Present: She writes every day.
Past: She wrote yesterday.
Future: She will write tomorrow.
Non-past (Present/Future): She writes now / She writes tomorrow.
Preterite (Simple Past): She finished the report.
Imperfect: She used to read by the window.
Present Progressive (Continuous): She is writing right now.
Past Progressive (Continuous): She was writing at 8 p.m.
Future Progressive (Continuous): She will be writing at 8 p.m. tomorrow.
Present Perfect: She has written three pages.
Past Perfect (Pluperfect): She had written the draft before the meeting started.
Future Perfect: She will have written the draft by noon.
Present Perfect Progressive (Continuous): She has been writing for two hours.
Past Perfect Progressive (Continuous): She had been writing for two hours before lunch.
Future Perfect Progressive (Continuous): She will have been writing for two hours by noon.
Conditional (Simple): She would write more if she had time.
Conditional Perfect: She would have written more if she had had time.
Habitual Past: She would walk to school every day.
